category comment: 

clue: Scrooge's 2-word response to "A merry Christmas, Uncle!"

response: "Bah! Humbug!"

clue: After recanting his belief that the Earth orbits the Sun, he's said to have muttered, "But it does move"

response: Galileo

clue: It's said William Booth sent his troops in this charitable "Army" a 1-word telegram: "Others"

response: the Salvation Army

clue: French title of Zola's 1898 letter to President Faure

response: J'Accuse...!

clue: The King James Bible's shortest verse, "Jesus wept", refers to the death of this man

response: Lazarus

